721656f-a.title: Manhattan: Minetta Street - Minetta Lane
721656f-a.text:
Minetta Street, north from its bend to Minetta Lane. At
the left are two 3-story buildings, No's. 12 and 14 that are to
remain and separate two modern 6-story apartment houses. The
preparatory stages of that one at the S. W. corner can be barely
perceived. This was reported in the N. Y. Times of December 16,
1939. A repnrt dated September 9, 1940 announces the second at
No's 2-1. This will be at the left mar; in.
The 3-story residence in the background is No. 16 Minetta
Lane and adjoins the warehouse at No. 12.
April 13, 1940
P. L. Sperr
NO REDRODUCTIONS
